The paper deals with the problem of learning the structure of a graph from noisy observations of epidemic cascades on the graph. This problem is related to social network analysis and machine learning, and involves algorithms and computational complexity. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Other likely sub-categories include cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.SD (Software Engineering), and cs.IT (Information Theory).
